<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// These methods are used to add different types of instructions to the alias</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// sets. Adding a new instruction can result in one of three actions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// happening:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   1 If the instruction doesn&#39;t alias any other sets, create a new set.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   2 If the instruction aliases exactly one set, add it to the set</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   3 If the instruction aliases multiple sets, merge the sets, and add</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///      the instruction to the result.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
